values:
I'm being a little self righteous son of a bitch and I know it and I can't stop it.

I hate my annoying passive aggressive little shit coworkers and they disgust me.&nbsp; I hate how they talk about my professor behind her back.&nbsp; I think it's abhorrently rude when they roll their eyes or say their little stupid sarcastic side comments.&nbsp; I hate it when they try to commandeer work and try to edge me out of the process.&nbsp; 

But the thing that I hate most of all is that I let them get to me and let them give my professor a reason to overlook all of that.&nbsp; I'm so disappointed that I disappointed an employer, inspiration and really good friend because of two people who are completely and utterly below me.&nbsp; I am so completely ashamed that I did not realize this sooner and allowed it to affect my cohesion with the research team as a whole and my ability to work with people despite how much I dislike them.&nbsp; And I'm saddened by the fact that no matter how many times I learn these lessons, they, for one reason or another, cannot seem to stick.&nbsp; 


I skipped Aikido today.&nbsp; What a horribly stupid stupid idea.

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I feel like I've begun to outgrow blogging in the recent month or so.&nbsp; Or maybe it's because I'm too busy doing stuff to actually write about it.&nbsp; It isn't as if I have not been experiencing things that I tend to blog about.&nbsp; It may just be that I'm getting better at dealing with them instead of throwing them to the hungry, anonymous (and not so anonymous) eyes of the internet.&nbsp; 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Or maybe it's because I'm losing the ability to express what I'm thinking about through something like a blog.

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A random observation that sparked this post to begin with:

I was on facebook, bored and procrastinating, of course, and I start coming across the names of people I definitely don't talk to anymore.&nbsp; It isn't even that we don't talk.&nbsp; It's that we don't talk, and the chances of us conversing ever again are slim to none.&nbsp; Then again, I'll probably be proven wrong when I head back to the States and we have conversations as if we were still in high school.&nbsp; But we're not in high school.&nbsp; We're different people now.

The voice of a friend of mine is still ringing through my head.&nbsp; Why do I have to keep pretending to be friends with these people?&nbsp; I want to stop pretending.&nbsp; I want to stop being a needy, brainless sheep of a human being that doesn't know when it's time to let go of the relationships that have become more of an obligation than something to maintain.&nbsp; 



It's time to take a renewed no bullshit pledge.&nbsp; If the connections I form with people are weak and meaningless, how can I expect anyone to value my friendship in the first place?&nbsp;

People despising me for no apparent reason is a serious pet peeve of mine.&nbsp; If you don't like me, there should be a reason.&nbsp; If there is a reason, you need to tell me.&nbsp; I'm not going to bite your head off, I'm not going to be absurdly offended.&nbsp; It is INFINITELY worse for someone to go through daily interaction wondering why you are looking at them like they took your first born son.&nbsp; 

What really pisses me off is that this person insists that nothing is wrong, but makes it SO transparent that they don't like me, it's almost above and beyond straight up telling me exactly what is wrong with me.&nbsp; I mean, if you are going to make the effort to be THAT obvious about it, why don't you just tell me so I can fix whatever pisses you off so much?&nbsp; Wouldn't that just make things easier for you and me?&nbsp; I wouldn't have the play the guessing game regarding what you hate about me, and you might not have to deal with what you hate about me if I fix it.&nbsp; Of course I can't fix it if I don't know what it is.

But of course not, that would be too simple.&nbsp; 

If you are a friend of mine, don't you dare do this, or I swear I'll just cut you out of my life forever.&nbsp; I can do it now too; I'm in Japan.&nbsp; I don't have to see your ass for a very long time if I don't want to.

No... really... I am...

In less than 48 hours I will be on a plane to San Francisco, from which I will be headed to Kansai International Airport in Osaka, Japan.&nbsp; I've never been so excited, scared, and unsure of anything in my life.&nbsp; As cliche as it sounds, this represents a great deal of individuation from my parents.&nbsp; I'll be studying and working part time in a country that, for the most part, does not speak English.&nbsp; I'm not coming home at all, even for Christmas, as the expense to do so is astronomical.&nbsp; 

To be honest, I don't think I'm ready.&nbsp; But I don't think anyone ever is.&nbsp; 





Let's do this shit.

I've come to this realization before, I think.

It isn't an issue of people liking me or not.&nbsp; People don't respect me.&nbsp; Maybe I just need the company of people too much to grow a backbone.&nbsp; I've been doing it for years.&nbsp; 

What do I do?

Why the hell is it raining?&nbsp; I wanted to take a run today.&nbsp; 


Actually, I probably would have made an excuse NOT to do it, but I guess the weather took care of that.


The only thing worse than suburbia is suburbia during rain.

I just took about an hour to really talk to someone after taking some pictures of the sunset.&nbsp; I could have been making headway on a really important stats project that I have to present in two days, but I'm glad I took the time to appreciate the little things in life.

Nostalgia has set in two years early.&nbsp; 

Hmmm...

At some point in my life, I lost all of my self confidence.&nbsp; Either that or I never had it.&nbsp; Or maybe it just disappears when I need it most.&nbsp; 

At Aikido, Holly told me that I had a beautiful voice.&nbsp; I was just fucking around and singing as I was getting to leave.&nbsp; And then of course I went and fucked up two solo auditions.&nbsp; Why?&nbsp; Because whenever I feel the pressure, my chest seizes up, my throat closes and my breathing becomes as shallow as a jock slut that's had a few drinks.

I really don't know why I can't just do shit right.&nbsp; This was my last chance and I fucking blew it.

The people I've met in the last few days have changed my life.&nbsp; They really embody a philosophy that needs to be applied to the way we teach our kids and the way we deal with one another.&nbsp; 

I have found two things in my life that make me very happy.&nbsp; I'm pretty sure this is the most stable and well grounded I've felt in a long time.&nbsp; I feel really comfortable in my own skin and it feels amazing.&nbsp; Some people never find anything in their life to make them really existentially happy, and I think I've found two?&nbsp; 


It hardly seems fair.

I've discovered that I'm actually a pretty competitive person.&nbsp; I really don't like losing or falling out of favor if it can be helped.&nbsp; 

That being said I'm irritated that my a cappella group seems to be resting on its laurels.&nbsp; Though those laurels are well earned, it'd be nice if we could learn some lessons from the people around us.&nbsp; I want more people to come to our shows and I want more people to be excited and have fun at them.&nbsp; Compromising the integrity of the group is always a concern, of course.

Sang well tonight, venue was shit, so much work, noreaster. &nbsp; 

BLARG!!!!!
